We can use grid to place elements in any order and in any shape

1.SPAN->it means how much grid cells(small squares) an element will occupy
2.ORDER->it means the order in which elements will occupy the grid cells
3.GRID AREA->it allows an element to occupy grid cells by specifying the indexes of lines

sample code

 .cowboy {
      background-color: #00B9FF;
      grid-column: span 2;
    }

  .astronaut {
      background-color: #03989E;
      order: 1;
      grid-column: span 2;
  }
 .astronaut {
      background-color: #03989E;
      order: 1;
      grid-area: 2 / 1 / 3 / 3;
    }
